Sentencas: This paper is devoted to a detailed study of the kinetic and thermodynamic characteristics of one of the most well-known solid oxide fuel cells cathode materials, La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) oxide, using the original oxygen partial pressure relaxation (OPPR) with macrokinetic model Tanks-in-Series (TIS) and quasi-equilibrium oxygen release (QEOR) techniques.
Titulo: Oxygen Exchange in MIEC Perovskite Oxide La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ: Kinetic and Equilibrium Parameters and Their Interrelation

Sentencas: Power-law dependences of kinetic characteristics on the partial pressure of oxygen and their Arrhenius dependences are shown.
Titulo: Oxygen Exchange in MIEC Perovskite Oxide La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ: Kinetic and Equilibrium Parameters and Their Interrelation

Sentencas: The equilibrium properties of the oxide are represented as continuous diagrams << T - pO(2) - delta >>
Titulo: Oxygen Exchange in MIEC Perovskite Oxide La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ: Kinetic and Equilibrium Parameters and Their Interrelation

Sentencas: It is shown that the Br & oslash;nsted-Evans-Polanyi homological approach is valid for LSCF and allows us to consider it as a series of delta-homologues involved in the same reaction with gaseous oxygen.
Titulo: Oxygen Exchange in MIEC Perovskite Oxide La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ: Kinetic and Equilibrium Parameters and Their Interrelation

Sentencas: The contribution of the entropy factor to the Gibbs activation energy is shown to be superior, which is typical for ferrites of ABO(3-delta) composition.
Titulo: Oxygen Exchange in MIEC Perovskite Oxide La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ: Kinetic and Equilibrium Parameters and Their Interrelation
